title: For Sale:  1943 Lee Enfield No. 4 Mk1 .303 British Rifle, Flawless Condition
postcontent:
I have a 1943 Lee Enfield No. 4 Mk1 .303 British Rifle for sale/trade.  Beautiful rifle!  Stock is in excellent condition, only treated with linseed oil to maintain it.  Smooth to the touch, a real pleasure to hold and shoot.  Has flip up sights added to it, a nice touch.  Everything is original and numbers matching, including the stock, barrel, receiver, magazine, bolt, etc.  Every part on the gun is stamped with the identical number.  The rifle is cleaned of all packing grease and shoots GREAT!  I personally have fired 10 rounds through it and I am extremely pleased to be able to shoot such a wonderful rifle.  The bolt cycles smoothly.  Much more pleasing to shooting than other WW2 rifles such as a nagant or mauser.  The rifling is EXCELLENT and shows that this rifle has seen very little use.  I have a No.3 enfield and when comparing the rifling, this No.4 enfield looks as if it's never been fired!

It's a shame to get rid of such a wonderful rifle.  I searched long and hard to find this rifle, and paid over $500 for it, but I recently got a speeding ticket and must relinquish this beautiful rifle from my collection.
If you want an excellent condition, firing Lee Enfield, look no further.  This rifle is beautiful to look at as well as shoot, and you can do both!

I am asking $475 for the rifle alone.  I have 2 brand new boxes of Hornady Match Grade .303 British rounds that I will sell with the rifle for a little extra if you need them.

I WILL SHIP.  But that cost is on you.  


I am also interested in trades:
The first thing I would trade for is a TAURUS JUDGE.  Definitely want one of those.
Interested in other handguns
Interested in other rifles and shotguns
I will take lesser value guns plus cash depending on the rifle, but don't expect me to add cash as I cannot right now.

WILL ADD PICTURES SOON.

title: For Sale:  The Challenge
postcontent:
Can you shoot 4 MOA rapid fire without a bipod or rest?  Can you do it with a rack-grade rifle and surplus ammo?  Can you do it with iron sights?  Join us for an Appleseed Rifle Marksmanship clinic and find out.

See if you can answer these questions - which every American who loves his country should be able to answer:
1. When and where was the American Revolution won, according to John Adams?
2. When and where did the Revolutionary War break out?
3. What caused the British Regulars, the most well-trained, well-disciplined army in the world, to break and run at Concord's North Bridge, after only two minutes of musket fire by shopkeepers and farmers?
4. What caused this reversal of British military opinion:

BEFORE April 19, 1775:
"Americans are raw, undisciplined and cowardly". John Montagu, 4th Earl of Sandwich and 1st Lord of the Admiralty 

"With a thousand British grenadiers I would undertake to go from one end of America to the other and geld all the males, partly by force and partly with a little coaxing". Major General Alured Clarke 

AFTER April 19, 1775:
"Whoever looks upon them as an irregular mob, will find himself very much mistaken. They have men amongst them who know very well what they are about..." Lieutenant-General Hugh Percy, 2nd Duke of Northumberland

Join us on April 13-14, 2013 for the Appleseed Rifle Marksmanship Clinic at the Northeast Kentucky Fish and Game Association in Cannonsburg, KY and find out the answers to these basic questions about our country's founding.
Cost varies by participant.  Pricing chart can be accessed via the following link:  http://www.appleseedinfo.org/pricing-new.html

Additionally, there is a $5 range fee.

For more information, go to:  http://www.appleseedinfo.org/search-states-location.php?locationid=285

title: For Sale:  BEWARE of SCAMMERS:  Colorado/Colorado Listings
postcontent:
WHAT is going on here! I have had a person claiming to be in Colorado then tell me they were in another state! Nothing replaces a face to face so that you can be comfortable in the transaction [No Thugs or Gangbangers] and you can see the weapon before you buy. This saves everyone time because if someone is trying to sell crap, then you can politely decline and move on. 

NOW I have see some sellers already trying to charge Hickenlooper fees and the law has not even taken effect yet (July 1st) 

And then I have had two seperate experiences where the seller tries a BAIT & SWITCH by offering a shotgun at a decent price, only to turn around and offer you one with less items (magazines & upgrades) but charge me several hundred dollars more!

This is more info I got from a seller: [I have also had people clame to be in Colorado only to find out they are in Arizona. I only sell face to face because I want the person buying anything to see it before they pay. Also in the past I have had people buy stuff and I ship it to them then they scream about the item being non functioning only to get it back and refund the money and find out parts have been stolen. On the Hickenlooper prices, once the mag ban goes into effect, you will not be able to LEGALLY buy or sell ANY detachable mags that have a removable floorplate. You will not be able to give them away or donate them, or sell them or loan them or buy or borrow them. I do hope the stupid anti gun laws get repealed but we must get involved and VOTE, if you do not vote you become part of the problem. Only voting can help the gun owners in Colorado. Also a new scam going around now is to sell a gun online, and when the buyer gets it, all they get is a box with a case and some rocks in it.]

REMEMBER: Avoid scams by dealing locally and NEVER send money to sellers without using a trusted escrow service. 

Be smart - Be Aware - Don't let these scum take advantage of you just like the Politicians have! FOR SHAME on those who wish to F**k honest people over! 

***If this posting makes one person slow down and THINK about what they are doing before falling prey, then it was worth the effort I put into it. I just made a FTF deal today and got what a great new present for my father. Glad he does not visit this site. -- Good People are Awesome & Armslist ROCKS!

title: For Sale:  WTS/T Carl Zeiss Hensoldt AG Victory Diarange 3-12x56mm laser range finding scope
postcontent:
I have a Carl Zeiss Hensoldt AG Victory Diarange 3-12x56mm scope for sale. Bought it from a coworker and to be quite honest, it's just simply way too much scope for what I intended on using it for. It has a class 1 laser range finder (eye safe) built in and can give almost immediate distance measurements in a 3 digit display at the bottom of the scope view. Scope is a FFP with, as expected, crystal clear glass from none other than Zeiss in Germany. It is illuminated reticle, and what I believe is the 60 reticle from Zeiss. I've spoken to their customer service dept and they can relatively easily change the reticle out for one of the Rapid Z-600 or Z-800 series if you prefer, but I haven't done that. The scope will come with the Zeiss mounting rails for mounting on your picitinny rail - these are the original Ziess manufactured rails that are no longer in production. There are no scratches on the lenses, no scratches/smudges on the scope body itself. With the exception of me putting in a new CR-123 for the range finder/illuminated reticle, this scope is basically brand new. I put it on an AR and put maybe 25 rounds down range with it mounted before calling it a day and taking it off. 
The good: Carl Zeiss Hensoldt AG Victory Diarange 3-12x56mm scope, original neoprene scope coat (Zeiss labeled), brand new CR-123 battery. No scratches, no damage, no occlusions - just a perfect, almost brand new Zeiss scope that has been extremely well taken care of and never abused. Original Zeiss mounting rails with specialty tool for taking it on/off (it's triangular in nature). Full, lifetime warranty as offered and covered by Zeiss. 

The bad: No box, no manuals, no paperwork. I have the .pdf that has the full manual in about 8 different languages, and can send it as an email attachment or you can relatively easily find it on line. The original tool that I received with the scope for the mounting rails (triangular in build) has some tooling marks on it and the single throw arm is bent a bit. I don't know if it is from some kind of damage - it's the way I received it from my coworker. I can take pictures of it later on and send them (currently at work). That's all the bad.

This scope is the same as this one shown in the [url=http://www.eurooptic.com/zeiss-victory-diarange-3-12x56-t-rapid-z-800.aspx]link[/url]
As stated above, currently at work and I don't have it here to take photos, but I can easily do so for serious buyers when I get home (4:30 PST).

I'm asking for $3500 shipped to US ONLY(insurance, tracking number, etc), which is what I paid for it, so I'm simply looking to recoup my outlay, which means you get to take $500 off a Zeiss scope and you're getting the $200 mounting rails for free, and I'm eating the shipping cost. Scope is located in northern NV and with the exception of me taking it to the range a few days ago, I'm pretty certain it's never seen the outside of a gun safe. I'd be willing to take personal checks - scope will not ship until it clears, USPS MO (max value of a money order is $1,000, so it would be a couple of them), certified funds (cashiers check, etc) or possibly paypal as a discreet gift....we can talk about the paypal. I mentioned I'm also open to trades as well, with my primary aim at getting relatively good long range optics for a 20" bull barreled AR, so please keep that in mind. Price is pretty firm, but I would be willing to work something out if it benefits both parties. Please give this scope a great home and take it hunting! :)

20-21 April 2013

Project Appleseed is an activity of The Revolutionary War Veterans Association, a 501(c)(3) all volunteer, non-partisan, non-profit organization, dedicated to teaching every American our shared heritage and history as well as traditional rifle marksmanship skills.  You may shoot anything from a .22 rimfire (the Ruger 10/22 and Marlin 795 are popular) to a centerfire such as an AR, AK, SKS, M1A or M1. Safe Rifle Handling - 4 safety rules

Steady Hold Factors

Natural Point of Aim
Sight adjustment using inches, minutes and clicks
The Story of Our Nation’s Birth
The Lessons of April 19, 1775
The Debt We Owe to Our Forefathers
The Duty We Owe to Our Posterity

Do you know when and where the American Revolution began? (It's not what you've been taught in school), Do you know where the War of Independence started? (It's not where you think). Lee 223 Factory Crimp Die crimps the bullet in place more firmly than any other tool. Tests demonstrate that even bullets which have no crimp groove will shoot more accurately. postcontent:
BRAND NEW in factory sealed package. Scope by itself retails for $200, so you're basically getting the binoculars for free (which retail for $115). Willing to ship for $15.00 extra.

Burris 3-9x40mm Fullfield II Rifle Scope w/ Burris 10x32mm Landmark Binoculars gives you a full spot-and-shoot package! This value package from Burris includes the Burris 3x-9x 40mm Fullfield-II Riflescope and the Burris Landmark 10x32mm Binoculars.

The Burris Fullfield II Rifle Scope has a one-piece main tube and eyepiece, Burris envied steel-on-steel adjustment system, and HiLume multi-coatings on every single air to glass lens surface. The Burris FullField-II Scope is even more forgiving for eye position, is a little shorter, and a good bit lighter. The magnification ring and eyepiece have been made into one solid unit requiring only two seals rather than three. To change magnification, simply turn the entire eyepiece. Burris Fullfield 2 Scope eliminated most of the potential leak paths in the eyepiece/power ring area and sealed the remainder with special quad seals instead of O-rings. The adjustment system has been moved to improve mounting options and the European-style adjustable eyepiece requires no locking mechanism. The Ballistic Plex reticle has a lower vertical crosshair with small ballistic lines that automatically compensate for bullet drop from 100 to 500 yards for many common cartridges. The Burris Fullfield-2 Riflescope is lighter, better sealed, and has a relocated adjustment system compared to the original Burris Fullfield.

The Burris Landmark Binoculars combine light weight, fully coated lenses and water resistant, fogproof construction. These Burris Binoculars also include a tough rubber armor coating and twist-up eyecups. Top all this off with a neck strap, carrying case, a full year warranty and a very affordable price and you have yourself a synonym for optical value.

Features of Burris 3-9x40mm Fullfield II Rifle Scope:

Waterproof: All Burris optics are proven to be absolutely waterproof. Each scope is submerged in water with a temperature of 50° C. The extremely hot water transfers its heat to the scope and the internal nitrogen expends 100% testing assures quality. Each scope is filled and purged at least 24 times with high quality, laboratory grade dry nitrogen. Each nitrogen cycle absorbs airborne and residual surface moisture that is evacuated from the scope. Burris uses specially made quad seals to provide double insurance against leakage.
Fog proof: The nitrogen contained in the scope is of high quality (ultra dry, laboratory grade nitrogen), ultra pure and ultra clean. To be sure that all airborne moisture and surfaces moisture within a scope is evacuated, testing consists of 24 cycles of pressurizing the scope and then subjecting it to a vacuum. The tests are both cost & time intensive.
Shock proof: Burris scopes are subjected to extreme recoil tests. An impact machine is used to measure and duplicate the recoil pulse acceleration and duration. This machine has been calibrated and verified by an independent laboratory to replicate the wave frequencies and shock impulses that a scope is subjected to.
Ballistic Plex reticle - with a basic crosshair reticle, calculating hold-over is a mix of art, science and just plain luck, which is why Burris developed the Ballistic Plex reticle. The key is the copyrighted lower vertical crosshair. With most common hunting cartridges, a shooter can use the reticle to compensate for bullet drop and aim dead-on at targets from 100 to 500 yards out. The need for hold-over guesstimation is eliminated. Using it is simple. Start by sighting-in your rifle at 100 or 200 yards at your scope's highest magnification. Then, once you determine the distance to your target, select the appropriate ballistic line. Add slight hold-over or hold-under for in-between yardages and take the shot.
Includes binoculars!
Burris Forever Warranty

title: For Sale:  SENATE TO VOTE ON "UNIVERSAL BACKGROUND CHECKS"
location: CONTACT YOUR SENATORS NOW., North Carolina, United States
postcontent:
Sometime next week the senate will vote on "universal background checks" which the Obama DOJ has already said will be ineffective without gun registration. This is what NRA-ILA Executive Director Chris Cox  has  to say about the matter:

"
Your Second Amendment freedoms are on the chopping block RIGHT NOW and ONLY YOU can save them.

Next week, your Senators are scheduled to vote on a so-called "universal background check" bill being pushed by lifelong anti-gun zealot, Senator Chuck Schumer. Schumer's bill would MAKE YOU A CRIMINAL if you simply transfer a firearm to an aunt, uncle, cousin or lifelong friend without the federal government's approval.

Even worse, President Barack Obama's Justice Department says that Schumer's bill will only be effective if it's coupled with MANDATORY GUN REGISTRATION.

Please call both of your U.S. Senators TODAY and tell them to vote "NO" on Schumer's "universal background check" bill. Simply call the Senate switchboard at 202*224*3121 and ask to speak with your Senators by name.

Call today, tomorrow, and put a reminder on your calendar to call next week too!

Think about it. Are criminals going to walk into a licensed gun dealer's store and fill out a federal form every time they want to give one of their criminal buddies a gun? Of course not! And Schumer knows it...he's just trying to play us for fools.

This isn't about making Americans safer...it's about leading law-abiding gun owners down the road to gun registration - and ultimately, GUN CONFISCATION - just like we watched happen in England and Australia.

So please, call your Senators RIGHT NOW and tell them to vote "NO" on Chuck Schumer's "universal background check" bill! Tell them you aren't fooled and they shouldn't be either!

And please, forward this email to your friends and family and urge them to take immediate action.

Thank you!!!

In Freedom,

Chris

Chris W. Cox
Executive Director
www.NRAILA.org

P.S. We can't leave anything to chance in this battle. So I've had our staff prepare tens of thousands of NRA-ILA's famous action alert postcards that we can mail to gun owners in key states. These cards can be in the hands of our best grassroots activists in a matter of just two days - perfect timing if we want to generate the thousands of phone calls we need to stop Schumer's anti-gun bill from passing!

But to get these cards in the mail I need YOU to make an urgent contribution to NRA-ILA today. If you give just $5 you'll cover the postage for 20 postcards...$10 will double the power of your grassroots activism by helping us mail 40 postcards!

Whatever amount you can afford to give, PLEASE CLICK HERE TO MAKE YOUR CONTRIBUTION NOW. Just a few dollars from you NOW will go a long way toward saving your freedom! But please hurry - we have to act FAST.

Again, on behalf of everyone here at NRA-ILA, thank you for your strong leadership and support! 
"

Further, do you trust the Obama administration with the ability to stop all legal gun sales simply by taking NICS offline? That's the power they will have with "universal background checks". And they will use any excuse they can find to do it. This is not about preventing crime. According to the DOJ report "Enforcement of the Brady Act - 2010" there were 72,659 failed NICS checks in 2010. Just 62 cases were even referred to federal prosecutors for criminal prosecution for giving false information on form 4473 or anything else. This is not about preventing violent crimes. It's another incremental step to controlling lawful gun owners. The Obama administration couldn't care less about enforcing the gun laws we already have.

title: For Sale:  Westinghouse Mosin Nagant 1915 M91 Hex receiver
postcontent:
For sale is a very hard to find Mosin Nagant M91 made for the Russians during WWI by Westinghouse in the USA. The order for these rifles was cancelled after the Russian Revolution, but most were shipped. This rifle is definitely one that was shipped as its condition is most certainly a war veteran.
The Soviets "scrubbed" the receiver markings of anything that was related to the former Czars. Thus, this receiver shows evidence of that being done by the Soviets, but enough survives to tell what it is. The NEW on the NEW England can still be seen as well as the TI in WESTINGHOUSE and the 191 of the 1915 date. It bears its original hex receiver but the serial numbered bolt does not match. Most likely replaced during a war rebuild. Stock is complete but has seen rough usage, bore is dark. it also has sling hangars typical of what the Finns used when they captured these rifles, but it is not marked with an SA stamp. 
Still in its cosmoline from being shipped from the former Soviet Union. Ah, if only these things could talk as to where they have been!
Will ship to a C&R or to an 01 FFL dealer for $35, insured.
Any questions, please ask.
Harold
